> Objective_2: Display cards with basketball players with all information about them (full name, position, league, career history)

App.js

1 ) Display the Card component for every player in the loop with the map function
— Call the map function on a players array
— Inside of a function read player as a function parameter
— Render the Card component and pass the player object inside as a prop
— Don't forget to pass a unique key prop for the Card component (React documentation).

Card.js

1 ) Display the career information in the loop with the map function
— Call the map function on a player.career array
— Inside of a function read career as a function parameter
— Render the Fragment component with a content provided in example
2 ) Use React.Fragment component as a wrapper to display career information.
— Only for Udemy exercises, not for real projects!!! Instead of doing import {Fragment} from "react"; and using it as <Fragment>...</Fragment> you should do import React from 'react'; and use fragment as <React.Fragment>...</React.Fragment>, otherwise you will have an errors and your content won't be rendered. (it's Udemy specific)
— Don't forget to pass a unique key prop for the Fragment component.